caption.p: ( a) Dendogram of the EO constituents of A. clypeolata from this study and from literature reports (the samples are marked according to Table 7); ( b) correlation network based on A. clypeolata EO constituents (CAM—camphene; SAB—sabinene; B-PIN— β-pinene; P-CYM—p-cymene; 1,8-CIN—1,8-cineole; CMP—camphor; BOR—borneol; T-4-OL—terpinene-4-ol; A-TER— α-terpineol; A-ARO—allo-aromadendrene; CAR-O—caryophyllene oxide; E-A-CAD—epi- α-cadinol; A-CAD— α-cadinol.
